===Hungarian Bácska===
[[File:BacsKiskunCounty.gif|thumb|right|230px|[[Bács-Kiskun]] County within [[Hungary]]]]
The Hungarian Bácska is mostly located in the [[Bács-Kiskun|Bács-Kiskun county]] of Hungary, while one small part of the region is located in the [[Baranya (county)|Baranya county]].

[[Subregions of Hungary|Subregions]] in the Hungarian Bácska include (with population numbers):
* [[Baja (Hungary)|Bajai]] (76,906)
* [[Bácsalmás]]i (18,578)
* [[Jánoshalma]]i (17,885)

Note that parts of Hungarian Bácska also belong to the subregions of [[Kiskunhalas]]i and [[Mohács]]i, although the main parts of those subregions are not located in Bácska.

Most important towns in Hungarian Bácska (with population numbers):
* [[Baja (Hungary)|Baja]] (38,143)
* [[Jánoshalma]] (9,866)
* [[Bácsalmás]] (7,694)

==Demographics==
[[File:Backa ethnic2002.png|thumb|right|250px|Ethnic map of Serbian Bačka (2002 census)]]
{{Main article|Demographic history of Bačka}}

===Serbia===
According to the 2002 [[Serbia]]n census, the population of the Serbian part of Bačka (in geographical borders) numbers 1,022,524 people and is composed of:<ref>Popis stanovništva, domaćinstava i stanova 2002. Knjiga 1: Nacionalna ili etnička pripadnost po naseljima. Republika Srbija, Republički zavod za statistiku Beograd 2003. {{ISBN|86-84433-07-6}}</ref>
* 559,700 (54.74%) [[Serbs]]
* 221,882 (21.70%) [[Magyar people|Hungarians]]
* others (including [[Slovaks]], [[Croats]], [[Bunjevci]], [[Šokci]], [[Pannonian Rusyns|Rusyns]], [[Montenegrins (ethnic group)|Montenegrins]], [[Yugoslavs]], [[Romani people|Romani]], [[Germans]], etc.).

===Hungary===
According to the 2001 census in [[Hungary]], the rough population of the Hungarian Bácska (including districts of [[Baja, Hungary|Bajai]], [[Bácsalmás]]i, and [[Jánoshalma]]i) numbering 113,432 people. [http://www.nepszamlalas.hu/hun/kotetek/06/03/data/tabhun/4/load01_1_0.html] Note that administrative borders of the districts do not fully correspond with the geographical borders of Hungarian Bácska. Most of the inhabitants of Hungarian Bácska are ethnic [[Hungarians]]. [http://lazarus.elte.hu/hun/maps/ke2500.gif]

