[[Image:Spout of Garnock.jpg|thumb|right|200px|The Spout of Garnock]]
The '''Spout of Garnock''' (or '''Garnock Spout''') is a waterfall in [[Ayrshire]], Scotland. At approximately 60–70&nbsp;ft high, it is the county's highest waterfall. It is not the source of the [[River Garnock]], as is sometimes said, but is located about a mile and a half from the river's birth.<ref>Love, Dane (2003). ''Ayrshire: Discovering a County''. Fort Publishing. p. 72. {{ISBN|9780954446116}}.</ref>

